Apparently originally a group of five, which somehow indicated a military formation and then came to refer to being arrayed for battle.
Assumes "all the fighting men [will cross over]." Could also be in apposition to "you" subject from previous clause. In either case, restricts "you" to the fighting men.
Assumes towards the sunrise (i.e., towards the east), which modifies 5676 (side).
